//Fri What does free really mean? To be free is to have the possibility to use your yearly revenue to live your life. If you reach an average revenue of 8% you should be able to use the revenue each year for all your expenses without seeing your balance decrease each year. Your requested revenue each month Your average revenue in % each year 8 What is your current balance? What amount can you save each month? You need How to get there? Use the calculator for interest on interest
//Rpr Interest on interest In short this means that you with regular investments and re-investments of your profit makes your revenue increase to a fortune over time. Lets say you have a balance of 100O and reach an average revenue of 8% each year. This means that you will have a balance of 1080 at the end of the year. With the same revenue the following year your balance has reached 1166 without further investments. With monthly investments the difference will be more obvious. Lets say you start with 300 and you invest 150 each month with the revenue of 8%: Year 1 gives you a balance of 2125 and your revenue is 25. Year 5 gives you a balance of 11000 and your revenue is 1700. Year 10 gives you a balance of 26700 and your revenue is 8400. Your monthly saving amount Your average revenue in % each year What is your current balance? For how many years are you able to invest? You will have Your revenue is You have invested *The revenue is calculated one time each year
//Info How to invest? You should try to invest at least 10% of your salary after tax. That way you will really see the benefits of interest on interest. Remember to spread your risks and do your research about the fund/company you about to invest in. Its way easier with funds instead of starting with the stock market. If you have a larger amount which you will use at the start of your investing career you have the choice to either invest all at once or to do it monthly over time. Its not easy to say whats right or wrong. If you decide you want to invest it all at once, you should be aware that if you have the bad luck of entering the market at a top, you will see your balance going in the wrong direction. Use Google to read about this as there are a lot of guidelines and information available around this topic. There are as many strategies as there are investors out there. Look around and see what fits your situation and personality. A good thing to do is to set up so all transaction is done automatically the date when you receive your salary. That way it will be easier keeping your regular investment strategy.
